Example


.bg-blue-500


Adding a hover state but only on medium screens:


.md:hover:bg-blue-500

Hover Classes

.md:hover:bg-{color}-{shade}   

.md:focus:bg-{color}-{shade} 



.md:hover:text-{color}-{shade}

.md:focus:text-{color}-{shade}


Example with the input field

<body class="h-screen bg-gray-200 flex justify-center items-center p-6">
        
<input class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded-lg py-2 px-4 block w-full" type="email" placeholder="jane@example.com">
        
</body>


So, lets add one of those modifier to the background

on small screens on hover bg-red-500
sm:hover:bg-red-500

<body class="h-screen bg-gray-200 flex justify-center items-center p-6">
        
<input class="bg-white sm:hover:bg-red-500 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg py-2 px-4 block w-full" type="email" placeholder="jane@example.com">
        
</body>

